parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire sidewall failure can lead to sudden loss of air pressure, causing the vehicle to lose control, resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Tire tread separation can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Valve stem failure can cause the tire to lose air pressure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the multifunction switch can cause intermittent or complete loss of turn signal, window, radio, and four-way flasher functions, leading to potential safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: and four-way flashers only work intermittently or not at all
causing uncertainty and danger on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The high-intensity discharge (HID) headlights can cause glare and blindness to oncoming drivers, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on rural roads and mountainous terrain.
symptoms: Oncoming drivers experience glare and blindness due to the overly bright headlights
making it difficult to see the road ahead and increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of issues, including stalling, loss of critical systems, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Various panel warning lights coming on
and issues with the inter-locking system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ability to operate the ignition switch without a key can lead to unauthorized vehicle use, theft, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ignition switch can be operated from the "ACC" to "RUN" or "START" position without a key
allowing unauthorized access to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate electrical connections between the vehicle and trailer can cause safety issues, including loss of critical systems and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Trailer plug coming out of the electrical plug-in
loss of headlights on the trailer
and issues with the electrical cord coming from the trailer.
